    bibo:volume "1884" ;
    dc:creator "Cohen, Rosa Graciela" ;
    dc:date "2008" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Branchinecta (Crustacea: Branchiopoda: Anostraca) from the Argentinian Tierra del Fuego" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184275>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184276>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184277> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184275>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Branchinecta fueguina nov. sp. male. A – E, Head rotated clockwise (up to down) from lateral-anterior to posterior view. F, head in dorsal view, arrow indicates a welt as seen from above. G, length of antenna 2 basal article (bal), taken in lateral view of the head (concave outline). H, length of antenna 2 distal article (dal), taken in anterior view of the head (convex outline). I, end view of the distal article; a: apophysis, Ant: anterior, eb: external margin, h: heel of apophysis, il: inner (medial) lobe, Post: posterior, w: welt. Scale bars: A – E, G – H = 800 μm; F, I = 1000 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184275/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184276>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Branchinecta fueguina nov. sp. male A – K, thoracic appendages series. L, apex of endopodite of 1 st pair of thoracic appendages. Setules are omitted. M, distal part of endopodite of 7 th pair of thoracic appendages. Setules are omitted. Arrows point at submarginal setae; N, Detail of apical setae of the first endopodite; a: sinuous setae, b: uniformly curved seta; scales at the base of posterior setae are omitted. O, gonopods; a: lateral view, b: ventral view, at: apical tuft, mr: medial cuticular reinforcement, pl: plumose setae, pc: pectinate setae, bi pc: bipectinate setae. Scale bars: A – K: 800 μm; L: 200 μm; M: 500 μm; N: 100 μm; O: 650 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184276/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.184277>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Branchinecta fueguina nov. sp. female. A, head in lateral view; lengths of antenna 2 (al) and spine (sl), taken in lateral view. B, brood pouch in lateral view; 1 st – 2 nd dm: first and second pairs of dorsal spiny mounds; le: lateral evaginations. Scale bars: A = 800 µm; B = 840 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/184277/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

